  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting at 6th level, your damaging cantrips affect even creatures that avoid the brunt of the effect. When a creature succeeds on a saving throw against your cantrip, the creature takes half the cantrip's damage (if any) but suffers no additional effect from the cantrip.</p><p>Additionally, if your damaging cantrips miss with an attack roll on your turn, you can reroll it. You can use this feature only once on each of your turns.</p><p>Furthermore, whenever you cast a cantrip that deals a type of damage from the following list, you can change that damage type to one of the other listed types: acid, cold, fire, lightning, poison or thunder.</p>",
